<CONTENT id="_3793166_1"><TITLE value="Presentation"/><TITLECOLOR value="#000000"/><DESCRIPTION
   value=""/><BODY><TEXT>&lt;p&gt;This is presentation for Session 9&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-43740565_1" alt="" width="125" height="101" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://youtu.be/44d1z9bc5JA" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;HIDS Vs NIDS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.indusface.com/learning/deep-packet-inspection-dpi/?utm_campaign=newsletter-april-2025&amp;amp;utm_medium=email&amp;amp;_hsenc=p2ANqtz--HNPzZv7XCneWT7-DYJLFYfnM-rpS_RvLDt0CQqWMhdJkGeFnhKG_sHrZZCoCAhoZyowqSeGTgJ0agG5DQmf6tJtcOe7hQ6Dc9DYrX2-ETdyNgpEY&amp;amp;_hsmi=356750153&amp;amp;utm_source=email-newsletter" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;What Is Deep Packet Inspection (DPI) and How It Works&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;Cyber Security Policy&lt;br&gt;&lt;a href="https://business.gov.au/online-and-digital/cyber-security/create-a-cyber-security-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Create a cyber security policy | business.gov.au&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cyber Security Procedures and Protocols&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; include the following instruction steps:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li style="list-style-type: decimal;" data-priority=""&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identify the assets&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;that need protection.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="list-style-type: decimal;" data-priority=""&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Protect the assets&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;by implementing security measures.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="list-style-type: decimal;" data-priority=""&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Monitor the system&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;for any security threats.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="list-style-type: decimal;" data-priority=""&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Respond to incidents&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;promptly.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li style="list-style-type: decimal;" data-priority=""&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recover&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;from any cybersecurity breaches.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note: Procedures&lt;/strong&gt; are usually formally formatted as a series of numbered steps to be followed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dynamic playbooks&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; contain these procedures are are used to direct users, depending on their pre-defined roles how to response to specific incidences.&lt;br&gt;The "dynamic" part means there are a choice to make from the number of "next steps" options to take depending on the results of the previous step.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p style="font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</TEXT><TYPE
   value="H"/></BODY><DATES><CREATED value="2023-07-24 13:40:45 AWST"/><UPDATED value="2025-04-16 12:23:35 AWST"/><START
